# Theme and styling

All visual values come from `@/theme`:

```typescript
import { border, colors, fontSize, spacing, text } from '@/theme';
```

Available tokens: `colors`, `spacing`, `fontSize` / `text.fontSize`, `border.radius`.

## StyleSheet rules

- Define styles with `StyleSheet.create` at the bottom of the file.
- Spread typography tokens: `...fontSize.md`, `...text.fontSize.md`.
- Use semantic colors: `colors.text`, `colors.palette.primary400`, `colors.palette.neutral200`.

```typescript
// ❌ BAD
fontSize: 16,
color: '#333',
marginBottom: 8,

// ✅ GOOD
...fontSize.md,
color: colors.text,
marginBottom: spacing.xs,
```

Do not add one-off hex values or magic numbers. If a token is missing, add it under `src/theme/` first, then use it.

Screens and components share the same token set — never fork ad-hoc palettes inside a feature.
